Some of his colleagues believe his daily intake of the stuff,
bought at some expense in Yemen and poured into his tea, is the
reason why he is still in action, travelling from country to
country, tirelessly pressing his cause. Indeed, despite being
troubled by Parkinson's disease, the Palestinian leader is still in
fairly good fettle. Alas, the same cannot be said of his
Palestinian state that may, or may not, now be approaching birth _
depending on the outcome of the tripartite summit in Camp David,
Md., which began Tuesday....By Phil Reeves, The Independent &QL;
