this why the Hezbollah fighters lost their hundreds of ``martyrs''
in their 18-year conflict with Israel and its Lebanese militia
allies? To blow up a war memorial? It stood atop a hill within
sight of Israel, the foreign land whom the SLA men had been paid to
defend. Of course, they were collaborators, Lebanese working for
their country's enemy. Some of them were brutal, cruel men. But
most of the dead were blackmailed by the Israelis into joining the
militia, boy-soldiers whose brothers or fathers would have been
imprisoned if they had not served Israel's cause in Lebanon....By
