<P>
   &UR; THERE ARE NO `ARABS' AND `ISRAELIS' AT CAMP DAVID &QL; 
 &UR; THE MACARTHUR GENIUSES: HOW TO BECOME ONE OF THEM &QL; 
 &UR; ALLISON FISHER IS THE TIGER WOODS OF NINE-BALL &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The following ``separate buy'' articles from SLATE, the premier
online magazine of politics and culture, are available from the New
York Times Syndicate. Please contact syndicate sales representative
DEBRA WEYDERT at 732-390-4480.
</P>
<P>
   1. THERE ARE NO `ARABS' AND `ISRAELIS' AT CAMP DAVID, by Anne
Applebaum
</P>
<P>
   Any Arab-Israeli deal at Camp David is virtually guaranteed to
produce angry, even violent opposition. Therefore, if a really
meaningful breakthrough is to be achieved, Ehud Barak and Yasser
Arafat will have to detach themselves from the factional, domestic
politics at home, ignore the probable negative consequences for
themselves and their political parties, cast aside petty concerns
about things like ``the next elections,'' close their eyes, cross
their fingers, sign, and hope for the best.
</P>
<P>
   And that's asking a lot of politicians.
</P>
<P>
   1,000 words: Slugged BC-UNLIKELY-SUMMIT-SLATE
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   2. THE MACARTHUR GENIUSES: HOW TO BECOME ONE OF THEM, by David
Plotz
</P>
<P>
   The MacArthur genius grant has become the United States' most
famous philanthropy project not because it rewards stellar people _
though it does _ but because it's mysterious. Several hundred
talent scouts, whose identities are secret, suggest nominees to the
selection committee. The committee, whose members are also secret,
covertly gathers dossiers on the nominees and selects two-dozen odd
winners.
</P>
<P>
   In a nation where self-promotion is a constitutional right, the
MacArthur is endlessly frustrating: You can't nominate yourself,
you can't nominate a friend, you can't lobby for it if you are
nominated. What's an unappreciated genius to do?
</P>
<P>
   Don't fear, the MacArthur is less cryptic than it seems. It can
be gamed. Here's how to improve your odds of becoming a certifiable
genius.
</P>
<P>
   1,200 words: Slugged BC-GENIUS-LESSONS-SLATE
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   3. ALLISON FISHER IS THE TIGER WOODS OF NINE-BALL, by Joseph
Nocera
</P>
<P>
   Nine-ball has become the default billiards game in both the
men's and women's professional circuits. And at the Woman's
National Championship, Allison Fisher is the Tiger Woods, the
Michael Jordan, the Wayne Gretzky, of nine-ball. Like them, she
makes the impossible look easy, and the difficult routine. Maybe
it's time for The Nine-Ball Battle of the Sexes.
</P>
<P>
   800 words: Slugged BC-CHICKS-WITH-STICKS-SLATE
</P>
