House were built largely by slave laborers, and now members of
Congress are looking to recognize those workers with a permanent
exhibit. Some are also hoping that new documents, demonstrating the
largely unrecognized and uncompensated contributions of
African-American slaves to the construction of the most visible
symbols of American democracy, will spur support for a belated
official apology for the long legacy of slavery. By Bruce Alpert.
