   BUSH-REMARK &QL;
</P>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Expecting fallout from angry teacher groups and
others about Gov. George W. Bush's comment on Wednesday about how
he hopes he won't be in Texas next year when the Legislature has to
cope with projected funding shortfalls. He shrugged off a question
about his own state's budget woes, saying ``as you know, I hope I'm
not here to deal with it. I'm seeking another office.'' By JAY
ROOT. Story will move in ``p'' political category. &QL; 
