<P>
   REVIEW-TOWNCAR _ A review of the Lincoln Town Car. (DeVault,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TELECOM _ WorldCom and Sprint have formally ended the deal that
would have led to a massive merger, bowing to regulators'
objections. The move does not signal the end of industry
consolidation. In fact, it frees both companies to negotiate with
others _ and there are talks going on. (Ebbers, in fact, hinted _
or joked _ that Deutsche Telekom ought to speak with him.) What
kind of deals are now likely? What is BellSouth looking at? And who
might be looking at BellSouth? Overview and analysis, in addition
to today's news. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TIMEWARNER-GA _ A Georgia Appeals court has upheld a $530
million verdict against Time Warner and other former owners of Six
Flags over Georgia. The park's new owner sued them in 1998 for
delaying the opening of the ``Batman'' ride and other
mismanagement. Time Warner says it will appeal but is taking a $50
million 2Q charge. (Kempner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   COMICS-MOVIES _ With the release of X-Men at movie theaters and
a host of additional superhero adventures on the horizon, including
Spider-Man and The Fantastic Four, here are a dozen do's and don'ts
of comic-book movies. (Larsen/Palmer, Dayton Daily News). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is a text/art package. Text by film critic Dave
Larsen, artwork/design by artist Randy Palmer.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   XMEN-REVIEW _ Review of the movie X-Men. Grade, B+. (Larsen,
Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-TIPS _ ``X-Men'' and its comic book heroes aren't your
bag? You'd prefer not to face a Wolverine sporting Freddy Krueger
claws? There are better than good movies out there. Just not always
a brand spanking new one. So here's a few recent _ and worthy _
movies you can see in new ways. Our recommendations include
``Croupier,'' ``Hamlet'' and ``The Old Man and the Sea.''
(BLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   MOLVIES-KADOSH _ Movie review: ``Kadosh,'' about ultraorthodox
Jewish society in Jerusalem. Grade: C+. (BLongino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 11.
</P>
<P>
   TV-ATLANTA-CHILDREN _ Review of ``Who Killed Atlanta's
Children,'' a docudrama on Showtime Sunday about the missing and
murdered children case of the early '80s. The movie itself is so-so
cable fare, but it bashes Atlanta heavily while strongly suggesting
(but never showing or proving) that white supremacists were
involved. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   TV-WEEKEND _ Phil Kloer's weekend TV viewing guide, including a
review of ``Nuremberg'' on TNT. (Kloer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   TV-NUREMBERG _ An interview with former U.S. Rep. Robert G.
Stephens, among those who served on the Nuremberg prosecution team.
Stephens, now in his late 80s,talks about the trial and about the
TNT series premiering Sunday. (He is not among those depicting in
the series). (McCarthy, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
