<P>
   OLY-TRACK _ Some call it the best track meet in the world,
better than the Olympics, because of the competition and pressure
to earn one of three spots on the U.S. team. No rubber stamp.
Michael Johnson, Maurice Greene and Marion Jones have to earn their
place. They're all in action during Day One. (Fish, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   OLY-GUIDRY _ Her resume includes two Olympic gold medals, a
World Championship gold medal, two U.S. Championship golds and more
NCAA gold medals and All-America honors than anyone in the proud
history of the University of Texas women's track program. But does
sprinter Carlette Guidry think her career been successful? Guidry
says yes. Bev Kearney isn't so sure. Kearney, the Longhorn women's
track coach, has been Guidry's personal coach since 1994. How much
longer Guidry will compete is uncertain, because the powerfully
built Houstonian _ she was known as ``Turbo'' when she arrived at
UT in 1988 _ will turn 32 on Sept. 4, just 17 days before the start
of the track competition at the Sydney Olympics. (Riggs, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   OLY-AUSTIN _ High jumper Charles Austin heads the list of
Central Texas athletes who begin competition in the Olympic track
and field Trials, which begin Friday in Sacramento, Calif. (Maher,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
