   COLOMBIA-MILITARY (El Sando, Colombia) _ A three-day rampage of
torture, rape and killing by a paramilitary group took place in
this tiny village last February, with no effort by military and
police units just a few miles away to stop the slaughter. The
incident _ at the very moment when President Clinton was pushing an
aid package to step up antidrug efforts in Colombia _ strikes at
the heart of the debate over the growing American backing of the
Colombian military. For years the U.S. government and human rights
groups have had reservations about the Colombian military
