   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ WACO, Texas _ During the 71st
All-Star Game in Atlanta I caught myself paying more attention to
the left-handed players. Earlier that day, I read a news story in
The Times of London that said homosexuals are more likely to be
left-handed.(Rowland Nethaway is senior editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MINTER-COLUMN _ FAYETTE COUNTY, Ga. _ ATLANTA _ I have been
pleased to discover, in Jonesville, La., someone who shares my
concern about e-mail, which has become all too popular and a
serious threat to intimate personal communication, and to a unique
way of recording history. Alma Womack writes a column for her
Jonesville parish newspaper. She sent a copy of one lamenting the
decline of old-fashioned letter-writing. (Jim Minter is a former
editor of The Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN _ DAYTON, Ohio _ This is not a time for
pettiness, but I can't help feeling peeved that, until last fall, I
appear to have been the only person in town who didn't know Joe
Belle. If he was Mr. UD (University of Dayton), Mr. Personality and
all that, don't you think he could have taken the trouble to call
me up? (McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
