   BRITAIN-WHITE-VAN-MAN (Leatherhead, England) _ In his hands he
has a wheel; in his ears, rings; on his arms, tattoos; and in his
heart, loathing for anyone he sees through his windshield. He is
known as White Van Man, and he is identified in motorist surveys as
the scourge of the stressed-out British road. That, at least, is
the popular caricature of the men who pilot the estimated 2.5
million commercial vans every day around Britain, a country with
the most congested roads in Europe and probably higher road rage
than any country on the Continent. A foreign journal by Warren
Hoge.
</P>
