<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIVE-MIDEAST-BOS </SLUG>
  
 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story MIDEAST-SUMMIT
(i) by Ann Scales and Charles M. Sennott, which moved Wednesday,
will wish to use the following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A Boston Globe article about the Mideast summit at Camp David
should have made clear that UN Resolution 242 does not refer to the
West Bank by name but calls for Israel to withdraw from territories
occupied in the 1967 war. The resolution, which formalizes the
principle of land-for-peace in the Israeli-Arab conflict, is
ambiguous on the amount of occupied territory from which Israel
should withdraw.
</P>
