<SLUG> BC-OLY-EVANS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INVITATIONAL ATTRACTS ELITE OF SWIMMING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Olympic gold medalists Jenny Thompson, Amanda
Beard, Kristine Quance-Julian, Claudia Poll, Amy Van Dyken, Dara
Torres and Brad Bridgewater, plus world record holders Lenny
Krayzelburg, Tom Malchow and Penny Heyns, are among the swimming
elite who will compete in the Janet Evans Invitational this weekend
at USC.
</P>
<P>
   More than 800 swimmers, including several national champions and
All-Americans, will participate in the event, which is the last
major meet before the Olympic Trials in Indianapolis Aug. 9-16.
</P>
<P>
   Also competing will be two-time national champion and five-time
NCAA champion Lindsay Benko, 1998 Goodwill Games medalist Erik
Vendt, and seven-time national champion Jennifer Parmenter, from
Granada Hills.
</P>
<P>
   The meet began Thursday with the 800-meter freestyle final. It
continues today with preliminaries at 9 a.m. and finals at 5 p.m.
The schedule is the same Saturday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets are $3 for preliminaries, $4 for finals and $5 for an
all-day pass. Children under six are free. Information: (213) 740-
8444.
</P>
</TEXT>
